    "ADL-LLM: An example of input and corresponding output.",
    "Input:The pool of examples E, the textual representation of the current window 𝑇 (𝑤 𝑡), an embedding function Φ, the number of examples to be retrieved 𝑘 ∈ N + Output: the 𝑘 examples from E that are the most semantically similar to 𝑇 (𝑤 𝑡) 𝜙 𝑤 𝑡 ← Φ(𝑇 (𝑤 𝑡)) 𝑝𝑎𝑖𝑟 𝑤𝑖𝑠𝑒𝐷𝑖𝑐𝑡 ← { } // Initialize an empty dictionary for (𝑇 (𝑤), 𝐴) ∈ E do 𝜙 𝑤 ← Φ(𝑇 (𝑤)) 𝑝𝑎𝑖𝑟 𝑤𝑖𝑠𝑒𝐷𝑖𝑐𝑡 [𝑇 (𝑤)] ← cosineSimilarity(𝜙 𝑤 𝑡, 𝜙 𝑤) end for return top 𝑘 examples in 𝑝𝑎𝑖𝑟 𝑤𝑖𝑠𝑒𝐷𝑖𝑐𝑡 Fig. 5.5Fig.",
